      "page_number": 1,
      "raw_text": "The bridge schemes still come\nin. The latest was filed with the\ncity clerk late yesterday and when\nread to the city council last night\nwas referred to the committee of\nthe whole. More than 200 prop\nerty owners living west of Monroe\nstreet signified their desire for a\nnew bridge at Cannon street. This\nwould furnish a ready outlet far\nTheir west than Monroe, and save a\nlot of travel. The site is ideal.\nThe bridge would reach from one\nrocky bluff to the other. People\nnow must use the Monroe street\nbridge, which means considerable\ntravel getting to it. One drawback\nin connection with the scheme is\nthat the. North Coast railroad\ntracks would be close to the north\nend of the structure. Councilmen\ngave the matter no discussion."
    }
  ]
